@node "versions" "Version history"

 @{b}Version's history@{ub}
 =================

  v0.xx  First screw-up's ;D
  v1.00  My first 'ready' version of AXOLR2. It contained couple of horrible
         bugs.
  v1.0x  Fixed bugs from version v.1.00
  v1.2   Minor bug improvements. First version without major bugs. This 
         version can be found from aminet:
         comm/bbs axolr12.lha
  v1.3   Minor improvements. Ready, but ugly :/

  v2.0   AXOLR II, fully re-programmed. Also totally new outlook.
         Old datafiles don't work anymore in this version. This version
         can be used with many BBS-software's. Many new options and more.
         No bugs (or?). Ready.

  v2.01  Now uses getopt() function to parse arguments.

  v2.02  Horrible bug fixed in argument parsing routine, fixed small color
         bug in yellow color (was darkyellow/brown in EGA colors).

@endnode
@node "future" "The future"

  @{b}The future@{ub}
  ==========

   It's my intension to translate AXOLR II for MSDOS and UNIX, and also do
   CNet version and add option which would remove ANSI-colors if needed.

   If you find bugs from program, or you have ideas how to improve 
   the program: tell about it to the author! It's allways nice to get 
   new ideas :)

@endnode
